gomodel:SYNGO_405  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 3: colocalization of ApoE with Synapsin I\nFig. 4: biochemical fractionation confirms synaptic localization of ApoE, colocalization of ApoE with vGlut1 and Map2\n\nNOTE: ApoE is a secreted proteins, therfore only synaptic cleft annotation is made. The colocalization with vGlut1 in synaptoneurosome showed in Fig.4 suggests that ApoE is localized at glutamatergic synapses.. Experimental description: Experiments with human brain tissue form buject with Alzheimer's disease or\nno cognitive deficits. These experiments are featured in Fig. 3 and Fig. 4\n\nLiteral M&M\n\"Subjects\nBrains from human subjects with a diagnosis of Alzheimer's disease or\nno cognitive deficits were obtained through the Massachusetts\nAlzheimer's Disease Research Centre and Massachusetts General\nHospital Neuropathology department.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_405" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

